    "Body": " Implementation A cost controller tracks, analyses and controls the costs associated with purchasing. On day-to-day basis, the role is responsible in forecasting expenditures, planning budgets, classifying costs by type, verifying supplier invoices. Prepare project cash flow. Forecast price and market trends to identify changes of balance in buyer-supplier power Perform cost and scenario analysis, and benchmarking against best market practices and market value for money data Conduct business review meetings with key stakeholders to assess risk Identify potential cost optimization and improvement opportunities. Align with procurement manager on proposed implementation actions Procurement and Inventory Management Seek and partner with reliable vendors and suppliers under the guidance of procurement manager Provide Procurement Manager and subsidiaries leadership with monthly financial data in order to allow them to analyse their performance and run their departments profitably. Communicate company needs to suppliers and maintain good relationships with top market vendors Negotiate contracts with suppliers. Ensure the company has all relevant information regarding all suppliers. Support procurement manager to ensure that purchases are within the working capital budget Maintaining acceptable and accurate inventory levels and ensure we keep accurate utilisation rates. Schedule and conduct monthly stock counts for the store items. Summarise results of monthly inventory counts to prepare and share consumption report, variance analysis and wastage report. Perform variance analysis of actual consumptions vs potential consumption and investigate differences. Ensure accurate and timely inventory reports are prepared and shared with Procurement Manager and management of business support. Monitor compliance of inventory policies and procedures Help initiate and manage the supplier registration process and ensure all new suppliers complete all required formalities Prepare RFQs/ RFPs as applicable, solicit and evaluate vendor responses to RFQs/ RFPs. Inform supervisor on responses Ensure that goods and services are purchased in a timely manner. Conduct site visits for key suppliers providing goods and services and document accordingly (as required) Ensure suppliers adhere to the highest ethical standards in relation to their work with the Group Receiving Ensure accuracy of the daily receiving report and that all items received, with or without invoice have been properly recorded thereon. Ensures that all invoices are reviewed and verified for completeness and accuracy, posted into the purchasing system and sent to the finance for payment processing. Verifies and prepare goods received without invoice list and send to finance. To spot check merchandise received daily to determine that it conforms to specifications as to weight, trim and count and that it has been properly invoiced. Ensures that adequate controls are maintained over all goods received from the point of receipt to the point of storage or final delivery. Reconciles total purchases for each month as reflected on vendor statements to total amount from receiving report for the month. Storage & Issuing Ensures that all merchandise is stored in properly locked storage areas and monitor security control keys for all such areas. Review merchandise storage practice periodically as to orderliness, price stamping and rotation of merchandise. Maintains a daily and cumulative monthly record of store requisitions and direct purchases issued to the producing department without requisition. Monitors procedure for issuing store items in the storeroom to ensure that such merchandise is issued only on written requisition signed by a duly authorized person. Internal Support Ensure proper documentation is maintained for transfer orders to relevant stakeholders internally and externally Create presentations using graphs, diagrams, and other exhibits to illustrate cost status to management Perform analysis of data stored in the project management and cost control systems. Communicate findings and proposes action plan for Procurement Manager\u2019s approval Track and report key functional metrics with an end goal to reduce expenses and improve effectiveness Align with supervisor on defining Key Performance Indicators. Generate a KPI Report on monthly basis to inform management. Ensure that policies and processes on purchasing, receiving, transferring, issuing are updated and observed in accordance to Internal Operating Procedures manual in order to be in line with Group\u2019s directives. Oversee/perform any other tasks in regards to day to day operations as requested by Procurement Manager Minimum Qualifications Undergraduate degree in in Accounting, finance supply chain management, procurement business administration or related field Certifications in supply chain management and/ or contract management will be preferred Certified Cost Technician (CCT) or Certified Cost Professional (CCP) would be considered favourably ?Minimum Experience Minimum of 5 years\u2019 work experience in a relevant field with experience in a purchasing division in Hospitality sector preferably in Middle East Demonstrable experience at all levels of the procurement process Proven experience in managing vendor relationships especially within the Middle Eastern region will be preferred Proficient in design, implementation and management of inventory control systems Job-Specific Skills Detail oriented personality Ability to effectively multitask Strong numerical skills Organized and Methodical personality Experience in conflict resolution techniques Excellent communication skills with emphasis in influencing others Strong understanding of procurement processes Decisive personality Solid negotiation skills Proficiency in office and specialized procurement software solutions. Modern e-procurement solutions would be an additional asset Fluent in English (written and verbal) ",
